Acetone washing for substance users - a harm reduction tutorial - jelly-reaction-b38.notion.site/ üßë‚Äçüî¨Acetone washing for substance users - a harm reduction tutorialSearchDuplicateTry NotionDrag image to repositionüßë‚Äçüî¨Acetone washing for substance users - a harm reduction tutorialOne simple method of cleaning your drugs is called an¬†acetone wash, a type of solvent wash. This will improve the purity of several drugs (the less soluble in acetone the better) if done correctly, but won‚Äôt remove any impurities that are also not soluble in acetone - for this you‚Äôre better off with a different solvent, or a different cleaning method altogether. A non-exhaustive list of drugs it can potentially help with:MethamphetamineAmphetamineCocaine HCl (the power form often sniffed, NOT crack/freebase!) (note also this will not remove levamisole!)MDMA2-CBFirst, a disclaimer:üö®Without lab testing, you as a layman can mostly only guess at purity and composition of substances. Reagent color change tests can help to identify pure substances, but are unhelpful at identifying mixtures - thin layer chromatography, which can be done at home with a lot, is better, but far from perfect.. Judging purity by weighing what you get out of a wash doesn't work, either‚Äî there's no guarantee that the residue is the drug that you think it is. Bioassay ("tasting it") isn't of any use because of the number of chemicals that can look and act similarly to each other. Acetone and other solvent washes are meant to remove certain cuts you know have been added (or impurities from the synthesis that weren‚Äôt removed), not to purify or isolate amphetamine or cocaine out of a mystery mix (for purification of amphetamine out of mystery mixtures, acid/base extraction is the gold standard). You can send drugs‚Äî pills, powders, or pastes‚Äî to¬†Drugdata¬†or¬†Energy Control¬†if you want professional GC/MS testing‚Äîthis is the only kind of test that will tell you exactly what substances are in your drug. It's anonymous and worth the money.WARNING!‚ö†Ô∏èAcetone and other solvents are flammable and should never be used around sparks or open flames (refrigerators, freezers, electric motors, furnaces). The vapours are volatile and can flash back to the container and cause a boiling liquid expanding vapour explosion. Always work with acetone in a well ventilated area and avoid inhaling the fumes. Have something to clean up spills, like vermiculite or cat litter (or paper towels or sawdust or something else absorbent) and wet it with cold water. Remember, acetone will eat many plastics, paints, and varnishes. How does this work?Well, the drugs you‚Äôd be washing in acetone aren‚Äôt very soluble in acetone, if at all, but a lot of impurities that might be in your drugs are! So the aim is to get the stuff you DON‚ÄôT want dissolved in the acetone, while the drugs you DO want are left behind.Supplies:Acetone - you want this to be pure, no added ingredients! To test if your acetone is clean, pour a little bit onto a clean glass/ceramic/metal surface and see if it leaves residue behind when it evaporates. If it doesn‚Äôt, you‚Äôre good. Acetone that is sold as ‚Äú100% acetone‚Äù will be pure enough (although it still contains water, see the acetone drying steps below). ACS grade acetone is the purest (but also the most expensive).Syringe (5 mL or larger luer slip, or oral syringe, is ideal for this) and cotton filter (qtip is fine) OR coffee filtersClean glass/ceramic containers with lids (do NOT use plastic unless you know they‚Äôre polyethylene, polypropylene, and fluoroplastics like Teflon, they will melt all over your drugs!)Mortar and pestle (optional but highly recommended)IF YOU ARE GOING TO DRY YOUR ACETONE (highly recommended):Epsom salts (magnesium sulfate - no added scents or other ingredients - for drying your acetone!) Really, plenty of dessicants would work here, if you have a different one you prefer, go for it. This section will focus on magnesium sulfate though.An oven or toaster oven A sealable jar to store your anhydrous acetone inWhy dry your acetone? Dry acetone has no water in it. Water in your acetone is less than ideal because even a little bit will cause you to lose some of your drugs. Acetone likes to hold on to water, and most of the drugs you‚Äôd be washing this way are also pretty soluble in water‚Äîcocaine especially, at roughly 2 grams per mL of water! That would amount to 50 mg out of a gram if the acetone had 0.5% water content and you used 5 mL of acetone‚Äîmaybe not a huge amount to sacrifice for many, but if you can avoid it by simply taking the time to dehydrate your acetone, why not? It can be time consuming, but once it‚Äôs done, it‚Äôs done until you need to make another batch. Still, it is ultimately optional if you don‚Äôt mind this potential loss.How to dry it: Crush up epsom salts in your mortar and pestle and put them in the oven on high (400-450 degrees F, or 200-250 C) for 3-4 hours. This will take all the water out of the epsom salts, and they will now absorb water from the atmosphere, or your acetone. You‚Äôll know it‚Äôs ready when it‚Äôs stark white with no transparency remaining to it. NileRed on YouTube has a great video explaining the process, which he does a little differently than laid out above (honestly, follow what he says where we disagree, I‚Äôm gonna edit above later to better reflect what he says): View originalPut the equivalent of roughly 1/5 of your container of acetone in dried epsom salts into the acetone container. It‚Äôs best to do this immediately after the epsom salts have dried because they will quickly begin absorbing moisture from the air. Give it a good shake for about a minute, and let it sit for a day. Make sure the lid is tightly closed. You now have dry acetone! Don‚Äôt shake the container after this point prior to use, and make sure to keep it sealed when you‚Äôre not using it - see end notes for further explanation.WASHING:Crush your drugs finely and put them in an acetone-friendly container of appropriate size‚Äîa shot glass works if you‚Äôre not washing a lot. Use your syringe to draw up the acetone, avoiding the epsom salt if you dried the acetone beforehand: 5-10 mL is recommended per gram of drug being washed at minimum, but more won‚Äôt hurt if you think you need it. (NOTE: if you store your acetone in the freezer and use it while it‚Äôs cold, the minuscule amount of your actual drugs it may absorb will be even less!) Pour your acetone over your drugs, making sure there‚Äôs plenty of room on top. The acetone will absorb impurities and some cuts, but not your drugs. Stir it around a bit with an acetone-friendly utensil (glass or metal) and let it sit for maybe 10 minutes. Then you have two options! Put a cotton filter (a q-tip works) or coffee filter in the acetone mix and draw up the excess acetone with your syringe through the filter. (Recommended)OR: Take a clean container with a new coffee filter covering the opening and wet the coffee filter with a bit of acetone. You can then pour in the contents of your shot glass. Save the coffee filter and scrape any residue from the shot glass. Let the acetone evaporate off and you can then retrieve your drugs from the coffee filter. IMPORTANT! Wait until your drugs are completely dry before using them! If they still smell like acetone, they aren‚Äôt dry. You can try hot plating‚Äîheating up a (microwave safe! No metal!) glass or ceramic plate in a microwave or oven until it‚Äôs almost too hot to hold comfortably‚Äîto speed up the drying off process if it‚Äôs taking awhile and you‚Äôre feeling impatient. Make sure not to apply heat directly to your drugs when heating your hot plate‚Äîas previously mentioned, acetone is flammable! Put the drugs on the plate only after it‚Äôs been warmed up by itself.End notesSo why does the dried acetone need to be stored in a sealed container? Acetone is hygroscopic, meaning it absorbs moisture readily from the air. If you leave it sitting uncovered for long, your acetone will start absorbing the moisture out of the ambient air. So keep it closed when you‚Äôre not using it! Note that this does also mean that you may need to re-dry your acetone eventually, especially if you‚Äôve left it unsealed for prolonged periods or topped it off.Sources:https://bluelight.org/xf/threads/simple-acetone-wash-for-meth-amphetamines-and-cocaine-pics-inside.725015/https://melmagazine.com/en-us/story/what-is-cocaine-cut-with-2http://tripproject.ca/increasing-the-purity-of-street-drugs/https://www.swgdrug.org/Monographs/COCAINE.pdfOther solvent washes
